            { q: "The four phases of the budget cycle are:", opts: ["Proposal, Review, Approval, Closure","Preparation, Approval, Implementation, Monitoring","Planning, Budgeting, Spending, Auditing","Drafting, Consultation, Enactment, Execution"], ans: 1, exp: "The budget cycle consists of preparation, approval, implementation, and monitoring and evaluation." },
            { q: "Charging expenditure to the wrong budget vote is known as:", opts: ["Budget variance","Misapplication of funds","Financial irregularity","Overspending"], ans: 1, exp: "Charging to a wrong vote is called 'misapplication of funds' and is a financial offence." },
            { q: "Who is the accounting officer of a Ministry?", opts: ["The Commissioner","The Director of Finance","The Permanent Secretary or Director-General","The Auditor-General"], ans: 2, exp: "The Permanent Secretary or Director-General is the Accounting Officer, personally accountable for all financial transactions." },
            { q: "The TSA (Treasury Single Account) is designed to:", opts: ["Allow MDAs to maintain separate accounts","Centralise all government revenue and prevent fragmentation","Provide petty cash to MDAs","Fund emergency expenditures"], ans: 1, exp: "The TSA centralises all government revenue into one account, preventing fragmentation and improving financial oversight." },
            { q: "A policy brief should typically be:", opts: ["50+ pages to be thorough","2-4 pages for ministerial-level briefs","Oral — not written","A classified document never to be shared"], ans: 1, exp: "A ministerial policy brief should typically be 2-4 pages — concise, evidence-based, and actionable." },
            { q: "The stage where government identifies which problems require attention is:", opts: ["Policy formulation","Policy adoption","Agenda setting","Policy evaluation"], ans: 2, exp: "Agenda setting is the stage where government identifies which problems are important enough to require action." },
            { q: "What should you do if someone asks to use your government financial system login?", opts: ["Allow it if they are more senior than you","Report it immediately — it is likely a fraud attempt","Share it only if it is urgent","Ask them to sign a form first"], ans: 1, exp: "Never share your login credentials. If asked, report it immediately — it is almost certainly a fraud attempt to implicate you." },
            { q: "The Office of the Auditor-General reports audit findings to:", opts: ["The Governor directly","The Ministry of Finance","The Lagos State House of Assembly","The Civil Service Commission"], ans: 2, exp: "The Auditor-General reports annually to the Lagos State House of Assembly, providing legislative oversight of government finances." },
            { q: "An effective policy brief must be:", opts: ["Advocacy-driven","Evidence-based and actionable","Lengthy to demonstrate thoroughness","Free of recommendations — only facts"], ans: 1, exp: "An effective policy brief is evidence-based, focused, actionable, and concise — not advocacy for a predetermined conclusion." }
