            { q: "What is the difference between correlation and causation?", opts: ["They are the same thing","Correlation means one thing causes another; causation means they move together","Correlation means two things move together; causation means one causes the other","Correlation is stronger than causation"], ans: 2, exp: "Correlation means two variables move together; causation means one variable directly causes changes in another — a critical distinction for policy." },
            { q: "A pivot table in Excel is used to:", opts: ["Calculate complex formulas","Summarise large datasets","Create charts and graphs","Merge multiple documents"], ans: 1, exp: "Pivot tables are used to summarise, reorganise, and analyse large datasets quickly and interactively." },
            { q: "When presenting data to decision-makers, you should:", opts: ["Show all the data in full tables","Lead with the key finding, then support with data","Only present data that supports your preferred outcome","Avoid charts — they can be misleading"], ans: 1, exp: "Lead with the key insight, use visuals, and support with data. Don't overwhelm decision-makers with raw figures." },
            { q: "A project is BEST defined as:", opts: ["Ongoing operational work","A temporary endeavour to create a unique outcome within scope, time, and budget","Annual budget preparation","Routine administrative processing"], ans: 1, exp: "A project is a temporary endeavour with a defined start, end, objective, and constraints — unlike ongoing operations." },
            { q: "Which process group involves formally completing the project and documenting lessons learned?", opts: ["Initiating","Planning","Monitoring and Controlling","Closing"], ans: 3, exp: "The Closing process group involves formally completing the project, documenting lessons learned, and handing over deliverables." },
            { q: "A Gantt chart shows:", opts: ["Organisational hierarchy","Financial budget allocation","Tasks on a timeline with dependencies and milestones","Risk likelihood and impact"], ans: 2, exp: "A Gantt chart is a project planning tool that shows tasks on a timeline, including dependencies and milestone dates." },
            { q: "'Scope creep' in project management refers to:", opts: ["The budget exceeding projections","The project timeline being extended","Uncontrolled expansion of project boundaries without approval","The team growing beyond planned size"], ans: 2, exp: "Scope creep is the uncontrolled expansion of a project's scope beyond its original boundaries without proper approval and resource adjustment." },
            { q: "What percentage of government IT projects are estimated to fail?", opts: ["10%","30%","60%","80%"], ans: 2, exp: "Studies suggest over 60% of government IT projects fail to deliver expected outcomes — making risk management critical." },
            { q: "The Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) is used to:", opts: ["Organise staff by department","Decompose the project into smaller, manageable tasks","Calculate the project budget","Plan stakeholder communication"], ans: 1, exp: "The WBS decomposes the project into smaller, manageable tasks, making it easier to assign responsibilities and estimate resources." }
